Date: Tue, 14 Apr 2026 17:06:21 +0000
Subject: [PATCH] feat(lanplay-bridge): integrate switch-lan-play relay via IPC
 channel
MIME-Version: 1.0
Content-Type: text/plain; charset=UTF-8
Content-Transfer-Encoding: 8bit

Wire ldn_mitm into the switch-lan-play relay so that wireless-local games
work over the internet.

IPC protocol
------------
Every outbound LDN UDP datagram is forwarded to 127.0.0.1:LDN_IPC_PORT
with a 4-byte destination IPv4 prefix:
  [4 bytes: dst IPv4, network byte order][LDN packet]

This single hook (LDUdpSocket::sendto override) covers both:
  - Broadcast Scan      (dst = 10.13.255.255)
  - Unicast ScanResp    (dst = 10.13.station.ip)

Changes
-------
+ lanplay_bridge.hpp/.cpp — status reader (sdmc:/tmp/lanplay.status)
  and lanplay_send_ipc() with a persistent loopback UDP socket
* LDUdpSocket::getBroadcast() — returns 10.13.255.255 when active
* LDUdpSocket::sendto()       — override: also sends IPC copy when active
* getFakeMac() / getNodeInfo() — use virtual IP (10.13.x.y) when active
* initialize() — skips nifmSetLocalNetworkMode(true) when active to
  preserve internet connectivity needed by the relay UDP socket
